By the example of all Apoſtolike Churches who had all of them corrupt members, and corruptions in them, in Doctrinein, Diſcipline, yet I never read of any that were beleeving that ever ſeparated or had any toleration ſo to doe; indeed the Apoſtle ſaith they went out from us becauſe they were not of us,1 Joh. 2 1 •
if they had beene of us they would have continued with us: falſe hearted profeſſors fell off and departed, but no believer, no Saint ſeparated. I ſpeake now no more how they were corrupted both the Church of the Jewes, Corinth,
Galatia, and the ſeven Churches of Aſia, of that heretofore; in Corinth there was that abuſe that I never ſaw in our Aſſemblies, the Sacrament given to a drunkard in his drunkenneſſe, as we ſee the text is there plaine for it, Some came hungry, ſome drunke; or drunkards have a little more ſhame, though they be drunke weeke after weeke, and day after day, yet when they come to the Lords table, they will be ſome body, for ſhame they will not then be drunke; if they were I thinke none would be ſo madde as to give the Sacrament to them.
